text: int main ( ) { int n , i , e , count ; int a [ 50 ] ; int dp [ 50 ] ; scanf ( "%d" , & n ) ; while ( n -- ) { count = 0 ; scanf ( "%d" , & e ) ; for ( int i = 0 ; i < e ; i ++ ) { scanf ( "%d" , & a [ i ] ) ; } dp [ 0 ] = 1 ; for ( int i = 1 ; i < e ; i ++ ) { if ( a [ i ] >= a [ i - 1 ] ) { dp [ i ] = 1 + dp [ i - 1 ] ; } else { dp [ i ] = 1 ; } } for ( int i = 0 ; i < e ; i ++ ) { count += dp [ i ] ; } printf ( "%d\n" , count ) ; } return 0 ; }
